00:09:01.870 --> 00:09:08.560
There are also quite a few things about western
farming that just fly in the face of the mythical
Jeffersonian yeoman farmer ideal.

00:09:08.560 --> 00:09:12.380
Firstly, this type of agricultural
work was a family affair;

00:09:12.380 --> 00:09:18.320
many women bore huge burdens on
western farms, as can be seen in this excerpt
from a farm woman in Arizona:

00:09:18.320 --> 00:09:20.760
“Get up, turn out my chickens, draw a pail of water …

00:09:20.760 --> 00:09:25.120
make a fire, put potatoes to cook, brush
and sweep half inch of dust off floor,

00:09:25.120 --> 00:09:33.560
feed three litters of chickens, then mix biscuits,
get breakfast, milk, besides work in the house and
this morning had to go half mile after calves.”

00:09:33.560 --> 00:09:42.340
These family-run farms were increasingly oriented towards production of wheat and corn for national and even international markets rather than trying to eke out subsistence.

00:09:42.340 --> 00:09:47.160
Farmers in Kansas found themselves competing
with farmers in Australia and Argentina,

00:09:47.160 --> 00:09:50.700
and this international competition pushed
prices lower and lower.

00:09:50.700 --> 00:09:58.140
Secondly, the Great Plains, while remarkably
productive agriculturally, wouldn’t be nearly as good for
producing crops without massive irrigation projects.

00:09:58.140 --> 00:10:03.080
